1705202,"age":66,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":77,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705207,"age":93,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705208,"age":95,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Julianne was born about 1492, in Suffolk, England. She married Thomas Cutler about 1517, in Ipswich, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters."},"et":{"Abt 1492–":"umbes 1492–Surnud","1501–1538":"1501–1538","–1557":"–1557","1523–1596":"1523–1596","1524–1586":"1524–1586","1526–1598":"1526–1598","1530–1579":"1530–1579","1538–1611":"1538–1611","–1590":"–1590","1492–Female":"1492–Surnud","Abt 1524":"umbes 1524","1558":"1558","1579":"1579","1557":"1557","1611":"1611","about 1517":"umbes 1517","1598":"1598","after 1538":"pärast 1538","1530":"1530","1596":"